name: "JFK" circa 1961
description: John Fitzgerald Kennedy served as the 35th President of the United States. He was seen as an influential figure with regard to both his foreign and domestic policies in the fight against communism. He was later embroiled in the failed Bay of Pigs Invasion and the Cuban Missile Crisis of 1962. Kennedy was assassinated in 1963 becoming the 4th US president to be assassinated.
